
bibtex2html produces HTML documents from a BibTeX file.

The invocation is

	bibtex2html <options> foo.bib

Options are:
  -s style   BibTeX style (plain, alpha, ...)
  -d         sort by date
  -a         sort as BibTeX (usually by author)
  -u         unsorted i.e. same order as in .bib file (default)
  -r         reverse the sort
  -nodoc     only produces the body of the HTML documents
  -suffix s  give an alternate suffix for HTML files
  -e key     exclude an entry

It will create a  file foo.html with the  list  of the BibTeX  entries
(the summary) and a directory foo with files  key.bib and key.html for
each key "key" in  the BibTex file. The  element of the summary of key
"key"  is a link  to the file  foo/key.html.   This file describes the
entry is more details: it gives the abstract  if a field "abstract" is
present, and links if  fields of the  kind  "url", "url1", "url2"  are
present. It also  give a link  to the field  foo/key.bib, which is the
BibTeX entry in ASCII format.


